column1: NGR is from 1950s record and is Bucks Copse Council Depot, the observer was the borough surveyor. Gauge moved here in May 1921. Altitudes are a reasonable match
There is a 2nd gauge at this location from Oct 1957 to Dec 1959 and the readings are very close with about 50% of the readings being identical, possibly suspicious

There are comments on the record for 1945 to 1950 mentioning another location at Reading Road. There is no evidence of duplication between the stations or even evidence of computed results. Readings have been left in this record
